
@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Index";
}

<div class="form-horizontal">

    <div class="form-group">
        <div class="col-md-12">

            <h3>Welcome</h3>
            <br />
                This application form is to be used to obtain a <em>Certificate Of Registration Of A Temporary Food Business </em>
                within the Hobart City Council area. <br />
                A certificate of registration is required if wish to hold a one-off food stall or sell food to the public.
                Do not complete this form if you are a registered mobile food business.
                <br />
                This form must be completed by the person responsible for the operation of the Temporary Food Business

        </div>

    </div>

    <div class="form-group">

        <div class="col-md-12">
            <h3>Application Steps</h3>
         

            
            <ul>
			<!--
                <li>
                    Read the <a href="http://www.hobartcity.com.au/files/f98018ca-0a1f-4173-a2cc-a01500c47e9b/Temp_Food_Stall_Guidelines.pdf" class="pdf">Guidelines for Temporary Food Stalls</a>
                    before completing the application form
                </li>
				-->
				<li>
                    Read the <a href="http://www.hobartcity.com.au/files/assets/public/public-health/food/temp_food_stall_guidelines.pdf" class="pdf">Guidelines for Temporary Food Stalls</a>
                    before completing the application form
                </li>
                <li>	Include as much detail as possible</li>
                <li>	Provide an answer to every question</li>
                <li>	Tick all the confirmations to complete the application process</li>
                <li>	Print your automatically generated certificate </li>
                <li>	Tick all the confirmations to complete the application process. </li>
                <li>	Contact Council to make payment - further details of how to do this are 
                provided at the end of the application process.</li>
                
            </ul>
            <p>
                Contact a member of Environmental Health Team on 6238 2715 if you need any assistance, 
                the application process should take approximately 10 minutes to complete.
            </p>
            <p>
                Once you have paid and your application has been assessed, you will receive your Certificate of Registration via email. 
                You are required to print and display your Certificate at the event. 
            </p>
            <p>
                Please be aware that food stalls may be inspected by an authorised officer.
                If stalls are found to be non-compliant with the DHHS Guidelines for Temporary Food Stalls infringement notices may be issued.

            </p>
            <p>
                Applications and payment must be made at least five (5) working days 
                before your event date. 
                If your application is less than five days before your event, 
                please contact a member of Environmental Health Team on 6238 2715 
                to ensure your application can be processed in time.

            </p>
            <p>
                @Html.ActionLink("Proceed to registration form", "Page1")
            </p>

        </div>

    </div>


</div>


